Defaulting to Recency
Ambiguity Trigger: An instruction that tells the AI to stop processing if the data is unclear.

Negative Constraint: An instruction that tells the AI what it is NOT allowed to do (e.g., "Do not assume").

Disambiguation: The process of resolving multiple possible meanings for a single word or phrase.

Reference Resolution: The technical name for the AI figuring out what a word like "it" refers to in the previous text.
Instructional Bleed—where the model gets so focused on its rules that it starts seeing them in the data even when they aren't there.

